com.preemptive.annotation.instrumentation

Annotation Type ApplicationStart


  • @Retention(value=CLASS)
@Target(value={CONSTRUCTOR,METHOD})
public @interface ApplicationStart
    Starts the application instrumentation.

    Application and company configuration information is garnered from the annotations in the class and method where this annotation is used, but blank or null information does not override defined values. If ApplicationVersionSource is used then other values for the version are ignored.

    Start needs the following information to start the application instrumentation:

    • Application ID - Required. See Application or ApplicationId.
    • Application Name - Optional. See Application or ApplicationName.
    • Application Version - Optional. See Application, ApplicationVersion, or ApplicationVersionSource.
    • Application Type - Optional. See Application or ApplicationType.
    • Application Instance ID - Optional. See ApplicationInstanceIdSource.
    • Company ID - Required. See Company or CompanyId.
    • Company Name - Optional. See Company or CompanyName.
    • Opt-in - Optional. See OptInSource.
    • Use SSL - Optional. See UseSSL.
    See Also:
    Application, ApplicationStop, ApplicationId, ApplicationInstanceIdSource, ApplicationName, ApplicationType, ApplicationVersion, ApplicationVersionSource, Company, CompanyId, CompanyName, OptInSource, PropertySource, FlowControl, SendInterval, UseSSL
